What is the best way to learn about a new subject?
To learn effectively about a new topic, try immersing yourself in the material by dedicating time and attention to understand it fully. Make sure you grasp the basics before moving on to more complex ideas so that you don’t get overwhelmed with unfamiliar terminology or concepts. Ask questions when necessary and take regular breaks when needed to avoid becoming burnt out. Utilize resources like textbooks, articles, videos, podcasts, etc., to supplement your learning experience.
